Package solver.reachablepoints.graph.board

Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • solver.reachablepoints.graph.board.Node
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    utility.game.board.IBoardCell<utility.game.board.CellValue>
    public class Node
extends Object
implements utility.game.board.IBoardCell<utility.game.board.CellValue>
    A cell of a board that holds information about all possible paths starting here. A path is represented as an edge. All edges are hold in an array and the index of the edge indicates the speed, direction and round-number you need to travel by this edge

        public ConcreteEdge getEdge​(utility.game.player.PlayerDirection direction,
                            boolean doJump,
                            int speed)
        Determines by a players location and State the edge he will travel.
        Parameters:
        direction - the players direction
        doJump - true for jump over the cells (when round % 6 == 0), else false
        speed - the players speed (1 <= speed >= 10)
        Returns:
        the ConcreteEdge or null if the requested edge is not passable
